description: Avoid travel outside US, immigration attorneys tell H-1B, F-1 visa holders
title: Avoid travel outside US, immigration attorneys tell H-1B, F-1 visa holders

description: Railway Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw highlighted significant improvements in railway safety, reducing accidents from an average of one per day to 30 annually. He also noted successful exports of locomotives and coaches, financial stability post-pandemic, and plans to increase the production of non-AC coaches.
title: Compared to Lalu era, train mishaps down 90%: Ashwini Vaishnaw

description: The Supreme Court raised concerns about lower courts denying bail in minor offences, despite completed investigations. They highlighted an increasing trend of such cases reaching the apex court. SC emphasized a need for a new bail law to ensure timely decisions, criticizing mechanical arrests and advocating for liberal grant of bail to protect personal liberty.
title: Denying bail in less serious offences unfortunate: Supreme Court

description: India has requested the US embassy to provide detailed expenditure reports of USAID-funded projects in the country over the past decade. Minister of State for External Affairs, Kirti Vardhan Singh, stated that this information, which includes financial details and involved NGOs, has yet to be submitted by the US, following allegations by Donald Trump regarding election funding.
title: India formally asks US for USAID spend info

description: An ITBP constable shot and killed his senior colleague after an argument in Raipur, Chhattisgarh. The incident occurred at the ITBP battalion headquarters. The constable fired 20 rounds from his Insas rifle, which resulted in the death of the senior officer. A detailed investigation into the incident is currently underway.
title: ITBP constable guns down senior after spat over dress code

description: China has expressed appreciation for PM Modi's positive statements and the successful meeting between President Xi and PM Modi in Kazan. Both nations are ready to work together to implement their leaders' understandings and promote stable development, benefiting over 2.8 billion people in both countries.
title: We stand ready to work with India, says China

description: Deputy CM Ajit Pawar acknowledged that financially well-off individuals received benefits from the Mukhya Mantri Majhi Ladki Bahin Yojana meant for poor women. The scheme will be corrected without reclaiming funds. Despite rising allocation for SC and ST outlay, the program continues, with a loan link of up to Rs 25,000 announced.
title: Ajit Pawar admits Ladki funds went to well-off too, vows to 'fix' it
Charges 'vague', says J&K HC, quashes detention of bar association ex-chief

description: Gamini, a South African female cheetah, and her four cubs were released into Kuno National Park, adding to the 17 cheetahs now in the wild, including 11 Indian-born cubs. With tourists receiving an improved opportunity to spot cheetahs on safari, MP CM Mohan Yadav highlighted this milestone in the cheetah reintroduction project.
title: Cheetah Gamini, her 4 cubs released into the wild

description: Mufti Munir Shakir, a vocal critic of the Pakistani state, was killed in an IED attack in Peshawar, leading to significant backlash against the ISI and military. His funeral saw mourners blaming Pakistani intelligence and chanting slogans against the army, accusing them of targeting Pashtuns.
title: ISI under fire after IED blast kills cleric known for criticism of Pakistani state

description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman has urged Indian industry to support the Prime Minister Internship Scheme, which targets providing internships to one crore youth over five years. The scheme aims to bridge the gap between industry expectations and youth skills, particularly in tier-II and -III cities, offering financial assistance to interns.
title: Join internship scheme, FM Sitharaman urges industry, launches mobile app

description: Gayatri Chakravorty Spivak has been honored with the 2025 Holberg Prize for her influential work in literary theory and philosophy. She has made significant contributions to fields such as comparative literature, translation, postcolonial studies, political philosophy, and feminist theory.
title: Kolkata-born Gayatri Spivak gets 2025 Holberg Prize

description: Maha man, 55, kills leopard to save dog
title: Maharashtra Psychologist, 55, kills leopard to save dog

description: Govardhan Dange, a farmer in Chandrapur, bravely fought off a tiger that attacked him while irrigating his field. Despite sustaining multiple injuries, he managed to escape by climbing into a well and calling for help. He is now recovering in a rural hospital.
title: Man fights off tiger, becomes a hero in Maha village overnight

description: An eyewitness from Hansapuri described the chaos caused by a masked group. "A team came here, their faces were hidden with scarves. They had sharp weapons, stickers, and bottles in their hands. They started the ruckus, vandalized shops, and pelted stones. They also torched vehicles," the eyewitness said.
title: Nagpur Violence: Clashes erupt in Hansapuri after earlier unrest in Mahal

description: The All India Muslim Personal Law Board led a demonstration against the Waqf (Amendment) Bill, joined by MPs from several opposition parties in New Delhi. AIMIM chief Asaduddin Owaisi cautioned NDA allies against supporting the bill, while opposition members claimed it was unconstitutional and divisive.
title: Opposition netas join AIMPLB protest against waqf bill

description: Women from Haryana are excelling in the military, with 34 cadets currently in the National Defence Academy. After the Supreme Court allowed women to take the NDA exam post-Class XII, there are now 121 women cadets. Women have been inducted since the 1990s but now also receive permanent commissions and can be promoted to higher ranks.
title: 121 women cadets in NDA, most from Haryana, govt tells RS

description: PM Narendra Modi and RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat will share the stage in Nagpur on March 30, marking their first public appearance together since the Ram Mandir consecration. The event comes amid speculation about BJP-RSS ties and coincides with BJP's preparations to elect a new national president.
title: Ahead of BJP president poll, PM Modi to meet Mohan Bhagwat

description: The Mumbai Economic Offences Wing arrested Javed Aazam in connection with the Rs 122 crore misappropriation case involving New India Cooperative Bank. Javed, the brother of BJP's former Maharashtra secretary Hyder Azam, was linked to the scam through businessman Unnathan Arunachalam, who claimed to have given him Rs 18 crore.
title: BJP neta's brother held in Rs 122 crore Cooperative bank scam

description: The Supreme Court has rejected former Gujarat IAS officer Pradeep Sharma's plea to discharge him from a money laundering case, emphasizing that economic offence proceedings should not be quashed without trial. SC clarified that money laundering is a continuing offence and does not conclude with a single instance.
title: Don't quash proceedings in economic offences without trial: Supreme Court

description: The number of foreigners visiting India for medical purposes has risen steadily post-pandemic, reaching nearly 6.6 lakh in 2023. Also, foreign tourist arrivals in the first half of 2024 showed 90% recovery compared to the same period in 2019, indicating a strong rebound.
title: Medical tourism on rise post-Covid, govt tells Parliament, launches portal

description: YSR Congress Party of Andhra Pradesh urges the Modi govt to clarify mechanisms ensuring southern states, which followed population control, do not lose political weight in the forthcoming Lok Sabha delimitation based on population criteria. YSRCP agrees with Home Minister Amit Shah on proportional LS seat increase but seeks details on implementation.
title: Need clarity on delimitation safeguards for south: YSRCP

description: US intelligence chief Tulsi Gabbard is optimistic about strengthening economic and trade ties between India and the US. She highlights that President Donald Trump and PM Narendra Modi are in direct dialogue to find solutions that benefit both economies, focusing on positive opportunities beyond tariff issues.
title: Trade talks happening at very top: Tulsi Gabbard
3 of Telangana family killed in US car crash

description: IIT-Bombay will implement more activity-based learning, hands-on training, and discussion-oriented classroom interactions from the next academic year. The initiative includes voluntary summer internships for first-year students to address local issues in their hometowns. Faculty, students, and alumni have collaborated to develop these innovative teaching methods.
title: IIT-Bombay innovation to take learning out of classroom
Indian radiographer suspended in UK for not knowing how to X-ray hand or foot

description: Lion sightings in Diu have increased, especially near forested areas close to Nagoa beach. On Sunday evening, a lion was spotted within 1km of the airport, causing traffic to halt as onlookers gathered to capture the moment. Forest officials directed the lion back towards the creek.
title: Lion seen lounging close to Diu airport

description: Security forces in Kashmir's Handwara district neutralized a Pakistani terrorist during a gunfight. The operation, which involved J&K police, the Army, and CRPF, was based on intelligence inputs. This was the first counterterrorism action in Kashmir this year since a previous incident in January.
title: Pak terrorist killed in Kashmir, first of 2025

description: Joshua Riibe, the 22-year-old Iowa man who was last seen with Sudiksha Konanki before her mysterious disappearance from the Dominican Republic resort, has now given the cops an ultimatum that he could not be detained by the police any longer. His attorney Beatriz Santana filed a motion in the court Monday that his client could not be detained any longer without being charged.
title: Person of interest in Sudiksha Konanki's disappearance case gives cops ultimatum: 'Can't detain any longer'
Punjab cops gun down suspect in Amritsar temple grenade attack

description: NASA has confirmed that astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore will return to Earth a day earlier than planned due to improved weather conditions. The astronauts, stranded on the ISS for over nine months, will be brought back aboard a SpaceX Crew Dragon capsule, with a splashdown scheduled for March 18.
title: Nasa reschedules Earth return for Sunita Williams and crew—here’s why

description: Alawieh has been in the US since 2018 when she came on a student visa. As Alawieh arrived at the Boston airport Thursday, she was denied entry as CBP officers started questioning her, searching her phone. Alawieh was asked about the photos and videos of Nasrallah and other Hezbollah leaders. She said she's apolitical and she received those photos on WhatsApp groups.
title: Religious, not political: Deported doctor on keeping Hezbollah leaders' photos on phone

description: President Trump plans to discuss ending the Ukraine war with Russian President Putin, focusing on territorial concessions and control of the Zaporizhzhia nuclear power plant. Trump aims to secure a 30-day ceasefire proposal accepted by Ukraine. Russia demands security guarantees excluding Kyiv from Nato membership. Britain's and France's peacekeeping force offer may aid truce enforcement.
title: Talks with Putin today on ending conflict in Ukraine: Donald Trump

description: Telangana CM A. Revanth Reddy has requested an appointment with PM Narendra Modi to discuss two bills proposing 42% reservation for backward classes in education, employment, and local bodies. Reddy seeks support from leaders of various political parties, all of whom backed the proposal in the assembly debate.
title: T'gana CM seeks PM Modi’s appointment over backward classes reservation bills

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai thanked SpaceX for launching the first FireSat satellite, part of an AI-powered constellation to detect wildfires. The satellite aims to identify fires as small as 5x5 meters using AI. The project involves partners like Earth Fire Alliance, Moore Foundation, and Muon Space, following Google's $13 million investment for enhancing global fire tracking.
title: Google CEO Sundar Pichai gives ‘special thanks’ to Elon Musk’s SpaceX for …
US' reply to French politician who demands Statue of Liberty back: 'Only because of us...'

description: Kolkata Knight Riders aim to secure their fourth IPL title with Ajinkya Rahane as the new captain. Retaining key players like Sunil Narine and Andre Russell, and adding talents such as Quinton de Kock and Anrich Nortje, KKR have a balanced squad. Despite a few weaknesses, their mix of experience and new additions positions them well for a successful season.
title: IPL 2025: KKR Team Preview – SWOT Analysis and Best XI

description: Lionel Messi will miss Argentina's upcoming World Cup qualifiers against Uruguay and Brazil. Coach Lionel Scaloni announced Messi's exclusion, likely due to a sore left thigh from a recent MLS match. Messi played the full 90 minutes for Inter Miami, but fitness concerns persist. Paulo Dybala, Gonzalo Montiel, and Giovani Lo Celso will also miss these crucial games.
title: Lionel Messi to miss World Cup qualifiers against Uruguay and Brazil
Nagpur violence: Sec 144 imposed, 'rumours led to religious tensions'

description: Star batter Virat Kohli has expressed his strong support for Rajat Patidar, the newly-appointed captain of Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB). Kohli believes Patidar is the future leader of the franchise and is confident in his ability to lead the team forward. Patidar succeeds Faf du Plessis and aims to live up to the high expectations.
title: 'He has got everything': Kohli backs Patidar to lead RCB for years

description: President Trump's tariffs on steel and aluminum have prompted varied global reactions, from Canada's forceful retaliation to Mexico's quiet diplomacy. The EU, China, and the UK are adopting differing strategies, causing economic uncertainty and diplomatic tensions. These responses highlight a reshaping of alliances and economic dependencies, with significant implications for global trade and security.
title: How to deal with Trump: Flattery, retaliation, or holding out?

description: Bihar Chief Minister Nitish Kumar may be preparing his son Nishant Kumar for a political role. Nishant has recently appeared in JD(U) events and posters, hinting at his potential political entry, which could help address concerns about Nitish’s health and the party's future leadership.
title: Is Nitish Kumar preparing for 'son'rise in Bihar?

description: Violent clashes erupted in Nagpur's Mahal area, with vandalism and arson reported Monday night. Vehicles were set ablaze and stone pelting caused panic among residents. Police intervened to control the situation, deploying additional personnel. Authorities are investigating the cause, urging locals to maintain peace and cooperate.
title: Watch: Violent clashes erupt in Nagpur, vehicles torched; cops injured

description: Ahmedabad-based Torrent Group has acquired a 67% controlling stake in IPL franchise Gujarat Titans, previously fully owned by CVC Capital Partners. Despite the transfer, CVC retains a 33% minority stake. Torrent aims to enhance the team's operations and growth. Founded in 2022, the franchise plays at Narendra Modi Stadium and has quickly become successful in the league.
title: IPL: Torrent Group acquires majority stake in Gujarat Titans

description: A video captures an Elon Musk look-alike in Pakistan enjoying a meal, sparking interest online. The Pakistani man's facial features closely resemble those of the Tesla and SpaceX CEO.
title: Pakistani tags Elon Musk, says: Look at your lookalike -- 'Pathan Elon Musk'

description: WWE Monday Night RAW on March 17, 2025, will feature John Cena’s return and face-off with Cody Rhodes in Brussels. Key events include Bron Breakker vs. Finn Bálor for the Intercontinental Championship and a contract signing for the Women's World Championship match at WrestleMania 41.
title: WWE Monday Night RAW: Full match, how to watch, and more

description: Delhi Capitals have overhauled their team for the upcoming 2025 IPL season with Axar Patel as the new captain. Wicketkeeper Abishek Porel expresses confidence that Patel's leadership will end the franchise's title drought, highlighting his deep understanding of the team and supportive off-field presence. Porel, who was retained by the franchise, highlighted Axar's deep understanding of the team, having spent six years with the Delhi outfit. Axar has been a part of the Delhi Capitals setup since 2019 and has become a crucial player in India's white-ball set-up too.
title: 'Axar is like a big brother ... Delhi Capitals will win trophy this year'

description: Gold continues to be a safe haven and wealth generator, with 17% three-year returns surpassing Sensex's 11.6%. With concerns about potential overvaluation and market instability, experts recommend cautious allocation within diversified portfolios.
title: Gold at record high! Check 5 charts before putting money in gold

description: Prime Minister Modi joined Truth Social and quickly interacted with US President Trump, thanking him for sharing his podcast link. Modi discussed a wide array of topics, including his relationship with Trump and ongoing India-US negotiations. Their exchange highlights their mutual admiration and current trade tariff discussions.
title: 'Thank you my friend': PM joins Truth Social after Trump's Fridman post

description: ​Srinivasan's attorney Nathan Yaffe said Kristi Noem's post was false and it showed that they were targeting Srinivasan. "Despite doing nothing wrong, Ms Srinivasan booked a flight out of the country to comply with US law, which gave her a 15-day deadline to depart after DHS illegally terminated her student status," Yaffe said.
title: 'Did not self-deport ...': Indian-origin student's lawyer refutes US claim

description: The National Board of Examinations (NBEMS) has confirmed that the NEET PG 2025 exam will be held on June 15, 2025. The exam will be conducted in two shifts: 9:00 AM to 12:30 PM and 3:30 PM to 7:00 PM. The internship completion deadline is set for July 31, 2025. Further details, including the full schedule, will be released soon. Aspirants can check the official NBEMS website for more information.
title: NEET PG 2025 exam to be held on June 15

description: ​American exceptionalism is a Will McAvoy speech wrapped in a Big Mac, and nowhere is this more evident than in the country's take on free speech—a delusion that is bipartisan, irrespective of whether one votes red, blue, or purple. Take a recent New Yorker piece titled The Detention of Mahmoud Khalil Is a Flagrant Assault on Free Speech, which, like all others in the same vein, operates under the assumption that Trump isn’t ceteris paribus but a unique, Agent Smith-like bug in the American simulation.
title: Not just Trump: Why crushing 'free speech' is a norm for America

description: Pakistan cricketer Khushdil Shah has been fined 50% of his match fee for a Level 2 ICC Code of Conduct breach during the first T20I against New Zealand. Khushdil collided with bowler Zakary Foulkes, deemed a careless contact. He accepted the charge, receiving three demerit points. Pakistan struggled, scoring just 91 runs, leading to a nine-wicket loss.
title: Pakistan star fined heavily for Level 2 breach after collision with NZ bowler

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi met with US Director of National Intelligence Tulsi Gabbard in New Delhi, discussing enhancing India-US defense and security ties. PM Modi gifted Gangajal, while Gabbard presented tulsi beads. Gabbard also held talks with Rajnath Singh and Ajit Doval on intelligence sharing and security collaboration, strengthening the strategic partnership between the two nations.
title: PM Modi meets US spy chief Tulsi Gabbard, gifts her Kumbh Gangajal

description: The entertainment world is abuzz with notable events: Virat Kohli discusses his approach to social media privacy with Anushka Sharma, Shah Rukh Khan may play a villain in Sukumar's next film, Alka Yagnik reacts to being Osama Bin Laden's favorite, Orry and others face legal action for alleged alcohol consumption near Vaishno Devi, and Imran Khan's relationship sparks controversy.
title: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: New Zealand Prime Minister Christopher Luxon humorously referenced recent cricket outcomes during a joint press conference with Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Luxon acknowledged New Zealand’s losses to India and highlighted the strong sporting ties between the countries. Both leaders welcomed a Memorandum of Cooperation on Sports to bolster collaboration.
title: Watch: NZ PM Luxon leaves PM Modi in splits during joint presser

description: China has praised Prime Minister Narendra Modi's recent comments, emphasizing dialogue and cooperation with India. Beijing noted progress in bilateral ties following Modi's meeting with President Xi Jinping and expressed commitment to maintaining stable and healthy relations, highlighting mutual benefits for global peace and prosperity.
title: 'Ballet of dragon & elephant': China praises PM's remarks on bilateral ties

description: Grimes, ex-girlfriend of Elon Musk and mother of his three children, highlights the difficulty of putting kids to bed as the hardest part of parenting. She shares her struggle through a Twitter thread, while also addressing falsely attributed claims about writing on the 'sexuality and kinks' of Fortune 500 CEOs, asserting her lack of control over replicated posts.
title: Elon Musk's ex on hardest part of parenting: I remember being a horror about...

description: Kannada actress Ranya Rao's bail plea in a high-profile gold smuggling case has been adjourned to March 19, with the court requiring the DRI’s objections. Arrested on March 3, 2025, with Rs 12.56 crore worth of gold, Ranya is accused of bypassing airport security using her police connections. The case has implicate influential individuals and intensified political controversy.
title: Gold smuggling case: Actress Ranya Rao’s bail plea adjourned till March 19

description: Sunil Gavaskar praised India's cricket depth after their 2025 Champions Trophy win despite Jasprit Bumrah's absence. He stressed no player, including Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma, is indispensable. Highlighting India's resilience and talent pool, Gavaskar noted the team’s strong comeback from a Test defeat to win against England in T20Is and ODIs.
title: No player indispensable, not even Virat Kohli or Rohit Sharma: Gavaskar

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi's motivation and dedication stem from the hard work he witnesses around him and his sense of responsibility to his country. He emphasizes serving the nation and adhering to principles of hard work, good intentions, and selfless service. His leadership inspires continuous effort and commitment.
title: Podcaster Lex Fridman decodes how PM Modi manages crazy work hours daily

description: The release of the Ibrahim Ali Khan and Khushi Kapoor starrer 'Nadaaniyaan' has sparked significant backlash and harsh criticism from the audience. Discussing the challenges faced by star kids due to nepotism and preparedness, industry experts emphasize the need for better training, support, and focus on the craft rather than glamor.
title: Are star kids judged too harshly? Ibrahim-Khushi trolled for 'Nadaaniyan'

description: Maharashtra Congress chief Harshvardhan Sapak compared CM Devendra Fadnavis to Mughal ruler Aurangzeb, sparking political tension. BJP condemned the remark as an 'insult to Maharashtra.' The controversy follows debates on Aurangzeb's tomb and Samajwadi Party MLA Abu Azmi’s praise of Aurangzeb, which led to his suspension from the state assembly.
title: 'Fadnavis as cruel as Aurangzeb': Cong leader's jab sparks row

description: Union minister Ashwini Vaishnaw announced the development of Asia's longest Hyperloop tube at IIT Madras, measuring 410 meters, with plans to become the world's longest soon. His visit to Chennai highlighted India's advancements in indigenously testing Hyperloop technology, with promising results and further development of electronic components at Chennai’s Integral Coach Factory.

description: Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge criticized PM Modi's government for not reducing fuel prices despite a 34% drop in global crude oil prices since 2014, accusing them of burdening the public and fueling inflation. Union Petroleum Minister Hardeep Singh Puri defended the government's policy, citing the benefits of the recently passed Oilfields Amendment Bill.
title: 'Modi govt robbing public': Kharge slams Centre over petrol prices

description: An 86-year-old woman from Mumbai was duped of Rs 20.25 crore in a 'digital arrest' scam running from December 2024 to March 2025. Scammers posing as police officers coerced her into transferring money, exploiting her fear of legal consequences. Mumbai Police are investigating.
title: Mumbai woman loses Rs 20 crore in one of India's longest 'digital arrest' scams
Ukraine truce deal: Putin & Trump to talk on March 18

description: Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis stated it is unfortunate that the government must protect Aurangzeb's grave amid calls for its removal. He emphasised adherence to legal procedures due to the site's protected status, ensured by the Archaeological Survey of India. Fadnavis lauded Shivaji Maharaj for his role in securing religious freedom.
title: 'Unfortunate that govt has to protect Aurangzeb's grave but ...': CM Fadnavis' warning amid row

description: Rajnath Singh raised concerns about Khalistani extremists operating on American soil in a meeting with US intelligence chief Tulsi Gabbard. They discussed enhancing defence and security ties. The talks also highlighted the activities of the banned Sikh For Justice organization. This meeting follows another between national security advisor Ajit Doval and Gabbard focusing on intelligence sharing.
title: 'Act against Khalistanis in America': India to US spy chief Tulsi Gabbard

description: BJP MLA T Raja Singh called for the removal of Mughal Emperor Aurangzeb's tomb in Maharashtra, asserting his aim to make India a 'Hindu Rashtra.' He echoed sentiments of various groups demanding the tomb's demolition, likening it to a 'poisonous sword.' Congress leaders criticized the demand, stressing it disrupts peace and hinders the state's development.

'Language not for hating': CM Naidu after his deputy's remark on NEP

description: BIS conducted raids at Amazon and Flipkart warehouses to tackle the distribution of substandard products supplied by Techvision International Pvt Ltd. Seized items included uncertified electronics and appliances. Legal action has been initiated against the involved entities, with BIS focusing on maintaining product safety and compliance standards.
title: Raids on Amazon, Flipkart warehouses linked to one company; Amazon responds

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore are preparing to return to Earth after spending nine months on the ISS. Technical issues with Boeing’s Starliner delayed their return. The recently launched SpaceX Crew-10 mission will facilitate their journey back. The astronauts continued important research and station maintenance during their extended stay.
title: Sunita Williams shares what she will 'miss' most about space ahead of Earth return

description: Pranshu Chauhan initially drove the car but later switched seats with Rakshit Chaurasiya, who took over the driver's seat. They left from a friend's residence, with Chaurasiya ultimately driving the car that caused an accident in Karelibaug, killing a woman and injuring seven others. CCTV footage helped reveal these details.
title: Watch: Footage shows Rakshit Chaurasiya taking driver’s seat before accident
Watch: Indian-origin missing student Konanki at outdoor bar with Riibe feet away

description: Inzamam-ul-Haq has raised concerns over the decline in Pakistan cricket, attributing it to poor decision-making and frequent changes in the PCB. He emphasised the need for a proper strategy and consistent planning to improve performance. Inzamam also supported Babar Azam, urging the board to trust the management and players to address issues collaboratively.
title: 'We will continue to fall ...': Inzamam criticises PCB over decline in performance

description: Peter Schiff warns that Bitcoin could crash to $20,000 if the Nasdaq enters a bear market. He emphasizes the historical correlation between Bitcoin and Nasdaq declines, while also pointing out gold’s potential rise as an alternative safe haven.
title: Will Bitcoin price crash to $20,000? Peter Schiff makes prediction

Defence experts stress the need for ongoing counterterrorism measures and suggest that high-level intelligence efforts are closing in on Saeed.
title: Abu Qatal killed — Could 26/11 mastermind Hafiz Saeed be the next target?

description: Maharashtra Cyber Cell summons comedian and YouTuber Samay Raina to record a statement regarding the controversial 'India's Got Latent' show, due to his absence in previous summons. The controversy began after inappropriate comments made by podcaster Ranveer Allahbadia, leading to FIRs and Supreme Court intervention. Raina expressed regret and removed all show videos from his channel.

description: A recent study highlights that over 57% of male corporate employees in India suffer from vitamin B12 deficiency, with nearly 50% of women also exhibiting low levels. Vitamin B12 deficiency is a growing concern among Indian men, particularly corporate employees with demanding work schedules. Prioritize your nutrition today to stay energized, focused, and healthy!
title: Over 57% of men lack vitamin B12: 6 diet tips to boost levels

description: Chinese daily Global Times commended Prime Minister Narendra Modi for his pragmatic approach towards improving India-China relations despite past tensions. PM Modi highlighted the importance of dialogue over discord during his podcast with Lex Fridman. Noteworthy progress has been made since the Kazan summit and recent border tensions are being addressed to restore normalcy.

'Turn to Lord Krishna's teachings ...': US spy chief Tulsi Gabbard

description: Prime Minister Modi and his New Zealand counterpart Christopher Luxon addressed a joint press conference in Delhi, highlighting agreements and discussions on bilateral relations, defence, security, migration, and terrorism. Modi emphasized their shared commitments in the Indo-Pacific and the strong sports ties between the two countries. They agreed to celebrate 100 years of sports relationship in 2026.
title: 'Will work together against terrorism': PM Modi after talks with NZ PM Luxon

description: Air Canada apologized after its in-flight maps replaced Israel with 'Palestinian territories.' The maps on 40 Boeing 737 MAX aircraft were deactivated, and Thales acknowledged the error. A rectified map will be installed starting March 14. Similar incidents have occurred with JetBlue, British Airways, and Swiss Airlines. Thales blamed a third-party provider.

Defence minister Rajnath Singh meets Tulsi Gabbard, discusses security ties

description: A scientific debate has emerged regarding the possibility of producing 'dark oxygen' without sunlight, through metallic nodules found deep in the ocean. The discovery challenges long-held beliefs about life's origins but faces skepticism and criticism from other scientists and the funding firm.
title: Do deep-sea nodules produce oxygen in the dark? Experts debate new findings

description: A tragic car accident in Vadodara, Gujarat, resulted in the death of a woman and injuries to eight others. Witnesses claim the driver, Rakshit Ravish Chaurasia, appeared intoxicated and was over-speeding. Chaurasia, now in custody, denies being drunk and attributes the accident to losing control after the airbag deployed. Victims demand strict action.
title: 'Overspeeding for enjoyment': Survivor recalls Vadodara car crash horror

description: A political conflict erupted in Tamil Nadu after the Enforcement Directorate claimed evidence of corruption within TASMAC. The BJP organized a protest, leading to the arrest of several opposition leaders. However, the DMK government has strongly refuted the allegations, denying any malpractices in TASMAC operations.
title: TASMAC scam sparks protests in Tamil Nadu; BJP leaders detained: Key details

He criticises President Trump's policy changes, including firing researchers and siding with tyrants. Glucksmann urges America to return the gift and invites dismissed researchers to work in France.

description: The IPL has expanded its player replacement policy, allowing teams to replace players facing season-ending injuries or illnesses till the season's 12th league fixture. Here's an explainer on what the rule specifically says.

Customers can enjoy ultra-fast internet, access to over 800 TV channels, and 11+ OTT apps by recharging with plans of Rs 299 or higher between March 17 and March 31, 2025.

Bolla's company employs over 500 people, and his inspiring journey is captured in a biopic starring Rajkummar Rao.

title: Trump shares PM Modi's podcast with Lex Fridman

description: Colaba residents urge legislative assembly Speaker Rahul Narwekar to halt the Rs 229-crore passenger jetty and terminal project at Radio Club near the Gateway of India. Their concerns include heritage impacts, traffic congestion, and environmental imbalances, urging feasibility checks before proceeding.
title: Why Mumbai residents are up against Rs 229 crore jetty near Gateway of India

description: NASA astronauts Butch Wilmore and Sunita Williams were on an extended nine-month mission aboard the ISS due to technical issues. Despite the prolonged stay, their compensation remains standard as federal employees, earning approximately $94,998 to $123,152 for the mission. They continue to contribute to scientific research, awaiting return on the SpaceX Dragon capsule.
title: Will Sunita Williams be paid extra for her extended stay in space? Here’s the NASA pay breakdown for her 9-month stay

description: CCB sleuths of Mangaluru City police arrested two South African women in Bengaluru and seized nearly 38kg MDMA worth Rs 75 crore. The suspects reportedly flew between Bengaluru and New Delhi 59 times in six months to deliver the drugs. The arrested are identified as Bamba Fanta and Abigail Adonis.
title: 59 Delhi-Bengaluru trips in 6 months: Two South Africans held with Rs 75 crore MDMA

description: In Bengaluru, the blooming season leads to increased bee activity and hive formation in urban areas. Residents and conservationists are promoting safe relocation over extermination to protect these vital pollinators and preserve biodiversity. Efforts include community education and advocating for humane hive removal practices.
title: A hive outside? Bee calm and get going

description: One of the assailants involved in the attack on Thakurdwara temple in Amritsar was killed during an encounter with Punjab police. The attack on the temple resulted in significant damage but no fatalities. The deceased was identified as Gursidak Singh, and his accomplice Vishal escaped. The police continue to pursue the remaining suspect.
title: Amritsar temple attack: Key assailant killed in police encounter, one escapes

description: Former Indian cricketer MS Dhoni recounted his infamous outburst during the 2019 IPL when a no-ball controversy led him to confront umpires on the field, resulting in a fine. Dhoni acknowledged his mistake while mentioning such incidents stem from the high stakes of the sport. He will play for CSK in IPL 2025, aiming to surpass Suresh Raina’s run record for the franchise.
title: MS Dhoni recalls 'big mistake' during IPL which 'triggered' him

description: Aman Putra Chand Khan, accused of raping a seven-year-old girl, attempted to escape police custody in Hathras, Uttar Pradesh by snatching a policeman's pistol and firing at the police. The police retaliated, injuring him in the leg, and he was subsequently recaptured and taken to the hospital for treatment before facing legal procedures.
title: Rape accused shot at while trying to escape from police custody in UP
RG Kar case: SC allows victim's parents to pursue CBI probe plea in Calcutta HC
Socialite Orry, 7 others booked for allegedly consuming alcohol at Katra hotel

description: During the interview, PM Modi discussed the significance of fasting in Indian culture, its spiritual and scientific aspects, and how it enhances sensory perception and discipline. The conversation also touched on PM Modi's vision for the nation.
title: The reason behind Lex Fridman’s 45-hour fast before his podcast with PM Modi

description: BJP state president K Annamalai was arrested by Chennai police while heading to Egmore for a protest against the TASMAC scam. Former Governor Tamilisai Soundararajan and other senior party leaders were also detained. Police blocked the residences of BJP state and district office-bearers from 7 am onwards, arresting them as soon as they attempted to leave for the protest.
title: TN BJP chief Annamalai, ex-governor Tamilisai Soundararajan arrested in Chennai

description: President Trump has declared that presidential pardons issued by Joe Biden are invalid, claiming they were signed with an autopen without Biden's knowledge. Trump suggested potential legal scrutiny for members of the January 6th committee, alleging they destroyed evidence and used the autopen for pardons without Biden's consent.
title: Trump declares war on 'sleepy' Biden's pardons: 'Void, vacant...'

description: US President Donald Trump has transformed the traditionally minimalistic Oval Office into a space filled with gold accents, grand portraits, and memorabilia from his Mar-a-Lago estate. His additions include replacing the Resolute Desk temporarily and planning for significant estate-style renovations to the White House grounds.
title: Trump’s golden touch: How Oval Office became a gilded palace
Goods train hits girder, disrupts traffic in Andhra Pradesh's Anakapalli

description: Congress criticised PM Modi for his podcast with Lex Fridman, accusing him of avoiding press conferences and attacking critics while claiming that 'criticism is the soul of democracy.' Modi discussed his influence from RSS, his stance on the Russia-Ukraine conflict, and his relationship with Donald Trump, aligning 'America First' with 'India First.'
title: 'Hypo(d)crisy ki koi seema nahi hai': Congress on PM Modi's podcast with Lex Fridman
J&K: Encounter breaks out between security forces and terrorists in Kupwara

description: Ukrainian President Zelenskyy accused Russia of prolonging the war despite ceasefire proposals and diplomatic efforts. He emphasized Ukraine's commitment to its defense and criticized Russian President Putin’s stance on the ceasefire as manipulative. Zelenskyy highlighted the importance of supporting Ukraine’s armed forces and condemned Russia for complicating the ceasefire process.
title: 'Russia stole almost another week': Zelenskyy on delayed ceasefire

description: BJP MLA Basangouda Patil Yatnal has vowed to reveal the names of ministers involved in a gold smuggling case associated with Kannada actress Ranya Rao. Rao, arrested with 14.8 kg of gold, is suspected of being part of a broader smuggling network. Investigations are ongoing.
title: 'Will name ministers linked to Ranya Rao gold smuggling case': BJP MLA

description: Iran-backed Houthi rebels in Yemen claimed a second attack on the USS Harry S Truman and its warships within 24 hours. This retaliation followed US airstrikes that targeted Houthi positions in Yemen, resulting in at least 53 rebel deaths and over 100 injuries.
title: 'Second time in 24 hrs': Iran-backed Houthis claim another attack on US ships

description: Ravichandran Ashwin reflects on his return to Chennai Super Kings (CSK) after a decade, noting the team's unchanged cricket-oriented nature despite the evolving corporatisation of the IPL. Ashwin, eager to enjoy cricket again, appreciates the familiar atmosphere and values the iconic bond with MS Dhoni.
title: Thank you Dhoni for getting me back to CSK: Ashwin
'Meet escalation with escalation': US, Houthis refuse to back down after airstrikes

description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal recommends HPCL and Varun Beverages as top stock picks. HPCL's strong refining margins and marketing volumes boost earnings, while Varun Beverages has seen significant revenue growth and expanded market penetration.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for this week

description: Sachin Tendulkar's India Masters clinched the International Masters League 2025 title by defeating West Indies Masters in Raipur. The match saw a heated exchange between Yuvraj Singh and Tino Best, requiring Brian Lara's intervention. Despite the tension, India comfortably chased 149 with Ambati Rayudu's 74-run contribution and Sachin's vintage performance, sealing victory with six wickets.
title: WATCH: Yuvraj, Best clash as tempers flare; Lara steps in

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore face significant physiological and psychological challenges upon returning from microgravity. They may experience muscle atrophy, bone loss, dizziness, and vision problems. Rehabilitation and NASA's support systems help them readapt to Earth's gravity and daily routines. The journey of adjustment after space travel is crucial for their recovery.
title: What Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore might experience after reaching earth

description: Top Lashkar-e-Taiba commander Abu Qatal was gunned down in Jhelum, Pakistan, by unidentified assailants. Qatal, a close aide of LeT founder Hafiz Saeed, was returning from a meeting with a Pakistan Army commander. The attack is believed to be due to infighting within LeT ranks. Qatal was involved in several terror activities, including attacks in J&K.
title: LeT ultra Abu Qatal, brain behind J&K attacks, killed in Pak

description: Two astronauts, Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore, are set to return to Earth on Tuesday evening after an unexpected nine-month stay on the ISS. NASA and SpaceX have revised the splashdown timing due to favorable conditions, allowing their return alongside another American astronaut and a Russian cosmonaut.
title: Sunita Williams's return to Earth moved up a day, set for Tuesday
Trump and I both put nation first, that’s our connect: PM Modi

description: Immigration attorneys report an increase in the secondary inspection and detention of green card holders by the US Custom and Border Protection (CBP), particularly targeting elderly Indian residents. Attorneys advise against surrendering green cards at the airport, stressing the importance of a hearing before an immigration judge.
title: US border officials target senior green card holders

description: In an escalating clash between the US executive branch and judiciary, Judge James Boasberg blocked President Trump's use of the 1798 Alien Enemies Act to deport Venezuelan gang members, including turning around flights already in the air. The Trump administration, challenging the ruling, claims it prioritizes public safety.
title: US govt deports migrants despite judge’s order
Trump, Putin likely to speak this week

description: The thriller drama 'The Diplomat,' starring John Abraham, has collected over Rs.13.30 crore in its opening week. Based on true events, the film highlights the rescue of Uzma Ahmed, an Indian girl trapped in Pakistan. The movie has received positive audience and critic reviews, particularly praising Abraham's performance.
title: ‘The Diplomat’ box office: John Abraham starrer earns Rs 13.30 cr in weekend

description: A man in Gwalior district killed his wife and staged her death as a road accident. Initial suspicions of foul play were confirmed by forensic and postmortem reports, which led to the husband's arrest. He and his family had been harassing the wife for dowry before her murder.
title: Inspired by shows, Gwalior man fakes road crash after killing wife to mislead cops

description: A priest, Mahendra Minekar, committed suicide at a temple in Kubernagar, Ahmedabad, allegedly due to the mental torture from authorities and developers over plans to demolish the temple established by his grandfather. Police are investigating the allegations, despite officials denying any demolition plans and asserting that the temple would remain intact during redevelopment.
title: Priest ends life, asks son in suicide note to ‘save temple’ in Ahmedabad

description: A 25-year-old woman from Ahmedabad filed a complaint against a man who insulted her height and hit her during an argument. The incident occurred while she was with friends. Police registered a case under Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita Section 74, involving assault with intent to outrage modesty, following her father's advice to file the complaint.
title: Ahmedabad event manager assaulted, mocked over her height

description: Punjab Governor Gulab Chand Kataria emphasized the importance of cow conservation in India and praised PM Narendra Modi for tackling political corruption. Speaking at the foundation of Tulsi Gaushala, he highlighted the historical reverence for cows and called for renewed efforts and research in cow welfare.
title: Cows possess magnetic power that wards off germs: Punjab governor Kataria

description: India and New Zealand have restarted discussions for a Free Trade Agreement after a 10-year hiatus. This new move aims to deepen economic ties and address market access issues to achieve balanced outcomes, as bilateral trade surpasses $1 billion.
title: India, New Zealand to restart FTA talks after a 10-year gap
EC looks to sort out legal issues for swift EPIC-Aadhaar linkage
